<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/739</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1662. Your 1138, February 16. Although rescinding of order forbidding
                                publication for thirty days of ships’ manifests comes at a time when
                                the public mind and press are occupied with more exciting subjects,
                                it is appreciatively received and will have excellent effect. The
                                    <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> this morning has thankful
                                comment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>